Background
OTC Derivative Marketplace
    As has been frequently noted, the growth of the OTC derivatives=20
marketplace has been dramatic over the past three decades. From its=20
beginnings in the early 1980s, when the first swap agreements were=20
negotiated, the notional value of these markets has grown to almost=20
$600 trillion globally. \1\ However, OTC derivatives were largely=20
excluded from the financial regulatory framework by the Commodity=20
Futures Modernization Act of 2000. As a securities and capital markets=20
regulator, the SEC has been particularly concerned about OTC=20
derivatives products that are related to, or based on, securities or=20
securities issuers, and as such are connected with the markets the SEC=20
is charged with overseeing.
