standards for dealers and major participants, and regulatory access to=20
and public transparency for information regarding security-based swap=20
and swap transactions. This series of rulemakings should improve=20
transparency and facilitate the centralized clearing of security-based=20
swaps, helping, among other things, to reduce counterparty risk. It=20
should also enhance investor protection by increasing disclosure=20
regarding security-based swap transactions and helping to mitigate=20
conflicts of interest involving security-based swaps. In addition,=20
these rulemakings should establish a regulatory framework that allows=20
OTC derivatives markets to continue to develop in a more transparent,=20
efficient, accessible, and competitive manner.
    Title VIII of the Act provides for increased oversight of financial=20
market utilities designated as systemically important and financial=20
institutions that engage in payment, clearing, and settlement=20
activities designated as systemically important by the Financial=20
Stability Oversight Council. The purpose of Title VIII is to mitigate=20
systemic risk in the financial system and promote financial stability.
