Group of Twenty (G-20) leaders have set out commitments related to=20
reform of the OTC derivatives markets that, when implemented by=20
national authorities, will form a broadly consistent international=20
regulatory approach. Work on the G-20 commitments is being done by=20
numerous groups of technical and policy experts, and staff members from=20
the Federal Reserve are actively participating in these groups.
    More generally, the Board participates in many international groups=20
that serve as vehicles for coordinating policies related to the=20
participants and the infrastructure of derivatives markets. These=20
groups include the Basel Committee on Banking Supervision (Basel=20
