amending rules that did not impact the economic interests of persons=20
holding open contracts. These changes recognized that the previous=20
system required the generation of substantial unnecessary paperwork by=20
exchanges and by the CFTC's staff. It slowed innovation without a=20
demonstrable public benefit.
