6. Requirements for Derivatives Clearing Organizations, Designated=20
        Contract Markets, and Swap Execution Facilities Regarding=20
        Mitigation of Conflicts of Interest\12\
    The Commission's proposed rules regarding the mitigation of=20
conflicts of interest in DCOs, DCMs, and SEFs (Regulated Entities) also=20
exceed its rulemaking authority under DFA and impose constraints on=20
governance that are unrelated to the purposes of DFA or the CEA. The=20
Commission purports to act pursuant to Section 726 of DFA but ignores=20
the clear boundaries of its authority under that section, which it=20
cites to justify taking control of every aspect of the governance of=20
those Regulated Entities. Section 726 conditions the Commission's right=20
to adopt rules mitigating conflicts of interest to circumstances where=20
the Commission has made a finding that the rule is ``necessary and=20
