business with, a [Regulated Entity] that clears or posts swaps or makes=20
swaps available for trading and in which such swap dealer or major swap=20
participant has a material debt or equity investment.'' (Emphasis=20
added.) The ``necessary and appropriate'' requirement constrains the=20
Commission to enact rules that are narrowly tailored to minimize their=20
burden on the industry. The Commission failed to make the required=20
determination that the proposed regulations were ``necessary and=20
proper'' and, unsurprisingly, the proposed rules are not narrowly=20
tailored but rather overbroad, outside of the authority granted to it=20
by DFA and extraordinarily burdensome.
