that affect all Regulated Entities, including those in which no swap=20
dealer has a material debt or equity investment and those that do not=20
even trade or clear swaps. Moreover, the governance rules proposed have=20
nothing to do with conflicts of interest, as that term is understood in=20
the context of corporate governance. Instead, the Commission has=20
created a concept of ``structural conflicts,'' which has no recognized=20
meaning outside of the Commission's own declarations and is unrelated=20
to ``conflict of interest'' as used in the CEA. The Commission proposed=20
rules to regulate the ownership of voting interests in Regulated=20
Entities by any member of those Regulated Entities, including members=20
whose interests are unrelated or even contrary to the interests of the=20
defined ``enumerated entities.'' In addition, the Commission is=20
attempting to impose membership condition requirements for a broad=20
range of committees that are unrelated to the decision making to which=20
