Protection of Cleared Swaps
    The CFTC recently sought comment \12\ through an Advanced Notice of=20
Proposed Rulemaking (ANPR) on the most appropriate customer protection=20
regime for cleared swaps. In our view the introduction of a customer=20
protection model that insulates clients from such fellow-customer risk=20
would best uphold one of the key aims of the Act--that of protecting=20
consumers. It would also ensure that the protections and safeguards=20
afforded to the U.S. client base are at least as strong as those that=20
will be offered to customers in Europe, as required under EMIR. \13\
